#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:110
msgid "Aperture"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:110
msgid "The lens aperture. The unit is the APEX value."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:111
msgid ""
"Name of the camera owner, photographer or image creator. The detailed format"
" is not specified, but it is recommended that the information be written for"
" ease of Interoperability. When the field is left blank, it is treated as "
"unknown."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:112
msgid "Battery Level"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:112
msgid "Battery level."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:113
msgid "Bits per Sample"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:113
msgid ""
"The number of bits per image component. Each component of the image is 8 "
"bits, so the value for this tag is 8. In JPEG compressed data a JPEG marker "
"is used instead of this tag."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:114
msgid "Brightness"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:114
msgid ""
"The value of brightness. The unit is the APEX value. Ordinarily it is given "
"in the range of -99.99 to 99.99."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:115 plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:159
msgid "CFA Pattern"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:115 plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:159
msgid ""
"The color filter array (CFA) geometric pattern of the image sensor when a "
"one-chip color area sensor is used. It does not apply to all sensing "
"methods."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:116
msgid "CFA Repeat Pattern Dim"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:116
msgid "CFA Repeat Pattern Dim."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:107
msgid "Color Space"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:107
msgid ""
"The color space information tag is always recorded as the color space "
"specifier. Normally sRGB is used to define the color space based on the PC "
"monitor conditions and environment. If a color space other than sRGB is "
"used, Uncalibrated is set. Image data recorded as Uncalibrated can be "
"treated as sRGB when it is converted to FlashPix."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:117
msgid "Components Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:117
msgid ""
"Information specific to compressed data. The channels of each component are "
"arranged in order from the 1st component to the 4th. For uncompressed data "
"the data arrangement is given in the <Exif.PhotometricInterpretation> tag. "
"However, since <Exif.PhotometricInterpretation> can only express the order "
"of Y, Cb and Cr, this tag is provided for cases when compressed data uses "
"components other than Y, Cb, and Cr and to enable support of other "
"sequences."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:118
msgid "Compressed Bits per Pixel"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:118
msgid ""
"Information specific to compressed data. The compression mode used for a "
"compressed image is indicated in unit bits per pixel."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:119
msgid "Compression"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:119
msgid ""
"The compression scheme used for the image data. When a primary image is JPEG"
" compressed, this designation is not necessary and is omitted. When "
"thumbnails use JPEG compression, this tag value is set to 6."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:120
msgid "Contrast"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:120
msgid ""
"The direction of contrast processing applied by the camera when the image "
"was shot."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:106
msgid "Custom Rendered"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:106
msgid ""
"The use of special processing on image data, such as rendering geared to "
"output. When special processing is performed, the reader is expected to "
"disable or minimize any further processing."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:87
msgid "Date and Time"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:87
msgid "The date and time of image creation."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:121
msgid "Date and Time (digitized)"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:121
msgid "The date and time when the image was stored as digital data."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:122
msgid "Date and Time (original)"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:122
msgid ""
"The date and time when the original image data was generated. For a digital "
"still camera the date and time the picture was taken are recorded."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:123
msgid "Device Setting Description"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:123
msgid ""
"Information on the picture-taking conditions of a particular camera model. "
"The tag is used only to indicate the picture-taking conditions in the "
"reader."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:124
msgid "Digital Zoom Ratio"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:124
msgid ""
"The digital zoom ratio when the image was shot. If the numerator of the "
"recorded value is 0, this indicates that digital zoom was not used."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:108
msgid "Document Name"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:108
msgid "Document name."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:125
msgid "Exif Version"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:125
msgid ""
"The version of Exif standard supported. Nonexistence of this field is taken "
"to mean nonconformance to the standard."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:88
msgid "Exposure Bias"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:88
msgid ""
"The exposure bias. The units is the APEX value. Ordinarily it is given in "
"the range of -99.99 to 99.99."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:126
msgid "Exposure Index"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:126
msgid ""
"The exposure index selected on the camera or input device at the time the "
"image is captured."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:89
msgid "Exposure Mode"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:89
msgid ""
"The exposure mode set when the image was shot. In auto-bracketing mode, the "
"camera shoots a series of frames of the same scene at different exposure "
"settings."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:71 plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:90
msgid "Exposure Program"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:90
msgid ""
"The class of the program used by the camera to set exposure when the picture"
" is taken."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:72 plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:127
msgid "Exposure Time"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:127
msgid "Exposure time, given in seconds."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:128
msgid "File Source"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:128
msgid ""
"Indicates the image source. If a DSC recorded the image, this tag value of "
"this tag always be set to 3, indicating that the image was recorded on a "
"DSC."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:129
msgid "Fill Order"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:129
msgid "Fill order."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:73 plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:91
msgid "Flash"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:91
msgid ""
"This tag is recorded when an image is taken using a strobe light (flash)."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:92
msgid "Flash Energy"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:92
msgid ""
"The strobe energy at the time the image is captured, as measured in Beam "
"Candle Power Seconds (BCPS)."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:130
msgid "FlashPix Version"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:130
msgid "The FlashPix format version supported by a FPXR file."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:74 plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:93
msgid "F Number"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:74 plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:93
msgid ""
"Diameter of the aperture relative to the effective focal length of the lens."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:75 plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:94
msgid "Focal Length"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:94
msgid ""
"The actual focal length of the lens, in mm. Conversion is not made to the "
"focal length of a 35 mm film camera."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:131
msgid "Focal Length In 35mm Film"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:131
msgid ""
"The equivalent focal length assuming a 35mm film camera, in mm. A value of 0"
" means the focal length is unknown. Note that this tag differs from the "
"<Exif.FocalLength> tag."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:132
msgid "Focal Plane Resolution Unit"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:132
msgid ""
"The unit for measuring <Exif.FocalPlaneXResolution> and "
"<Exif.FocalPlaneYResolution>. This value is the same as the "
"<Exif.ResolutionUnit>."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:133
msgid "Focal Plane x-Resolution"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:133
msgid ""
"The number of pixels in the image width (X) direction per "
"<Exif.FocalPlaneResolutionUnit> on the camera focal plane."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:134
msgid "Focal Plane y-Resolution"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:134
msgid ""
"The number of pixels in the image height (Y) direction per "
"<Exif.FocalPlaneResolutionUnit> on the camera focal plane."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:135
msgid "Gain Control"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:135
msgid "This tag indicates the degree of overall image gain adjustment."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:136
msgid "Gamma"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:136
msgid "Indicates the value of coefficient gamma."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:137
msgid "Altitude"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:137
msgid ""
"Indicates the altitude based on the reference in <Exif.GPS.AltitudeRef>. The"
" reference unit is meters."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:138
msgid "Altitude Reference"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:138
msgid ""
"Indicates the altitude used as the reference altitude. If the reference is "
"sea level and the altitude is above sea level, 0 is given. If the altitude "
"is below sea level, a value of 1 is given and the altitude is indicated as "
"an absolute value in the <Exif.GPS.Altitude> tag. The reference unit is "
"meters."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:139
msgid "GPS Info IFDPointer"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:139
msgid ""
"A pointer to the GPS Info IFD. The Interoperability structure of the GPS "
"Info IFD, like that of Exif IFD, has no image data."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:140
msgid "Latitude"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:140
msgid ""
"Indicates the latitude. The latitude is expressed as three RATIONAL values "
"giving the degrees, minutes, and seconds, respectively. When degrees, "
"minutes and seconds are expressed, the format is dd/1,mm/1,ss/1. When "
"degrees and minutes are used and, for example, fractions of minutes are "
"given up to two decimal places, the format is dd/1,mmmm/100,0/1."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:141
msgid "North or South Latitude"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:142
msgid "Longitude"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:142
msgid ""
"Indicates the longitude. The longitude is expressed as three RATIONAL values"
" giving the degrees, minutes, and seconds, respectively. When degrees, "
"minutes and seconds are expressed, the format is ddd/1,mm/1,ss/1. When "
"degrees and minutes are used and, for example, fractions of minutes are "
"given up to two decimal places, the format is ddd/1,mmmm/100,0/1."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:143
msgid "East or West Longitude"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:144
msgid "GPS Tag Version"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:144
msgid ""
"Indicates the version of <Exif.GPS.InfoIFD>. This tag is mandatory when "
"<Exif.GPS.Info> tag is present."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:145
msgid "Image Description"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:145
msgid ""
"A character string giving the title of the image. Two-bytes character codes "
"cannot be used. When a 2-bytes code is necessary, the Exif Private tag "
"<Exif.UserComment> is to be used."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:104
msgid "Image Length"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:104
msgid ""
"The number of rows of image data. In JPEG compressed data a JPEG marker is "
"used instead of this tag."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:146
msgid "Image Resources Block"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:146
msgid "Image Resources Block."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:147
msgid "Image Unique ID"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:147
msgid ""
"This tag indicates an identifier assigned uniquely to each image. It is "
"recorded as an ASCII string equivalent to hexadecimal notation and 128-bit "
"fixed length."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:105
msgid "Image Width"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:105
msgid ""
"The number of columns of image data, equal to the number of pixels per row. "
"In JPEG compressed data a JPEG marker is used instead of this tag."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:148
msgid "Inter Color Profile"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:148
msgid "Inter Color Profile."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:149
msgid "Interoperability Index"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:150
msgid "Interoperability Version"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:150
msgid "Interoperability version."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:151
msgid "An IPTC/NAA record."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:95
msgid "ISO Speed Ratings"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:95
msgid ""
"The ISO Speed and ISO Latitude of the camera or input device as specified in"
" ISO 12232."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:152
msgid "JPEG Interchange Format"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:152
msgid ""
"The offset to the start byte (SOI) of JPEG compressed thumbnail data. This "
"is not used for primary image JPEG data."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:153
msgid "JPEG Interchange Format Length"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:153
msgid ""
"The number of bytes of JPEG compressed thumbnail data. This is not used for "
"primary image JPEG data. JPEG thumbnails are not divided but are recorded as"
" a continuous JPEG bitstream from SOI to EOI. Appn and COM markers should "
"not be recorded. Compressed thumbnails must be recorded in no more than 64 "
"Kbytes, including all other data to be recorded in APP1."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:154
msgid "JPEG Procedure"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:154
msgid "JPEG procedure."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:155
msgid "Light Source"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:155
msgid "The kind of light source."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:156
msgid "Manufacturer"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:156
msgid ""
"The manufacturer of the recording equipment. This is the manufacturer of the"
" DSC, scanner, video digitizer or other equipment that generated the image. "
"When the field is left blank, it is treated as unknown."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:157
msgid "Maker Note"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:157
msgid ""
"A tag for manufacturers of Exif writers to record any desired information. "
"The contents are up to the manufacturer."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:96
msgid "Max Aperture Value"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:96
msgid ""
"The smallest F number of the lens. The unit is the APEX value. Ordinarily it"
" is given in the range of 00.00 to 99.99, but it is not limited to this "
"range."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:78 plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:97
msgid "Metering Mode"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:97
msgid "The metering mode."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:65 plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:158
msgid "Model"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:158
msgid ""
"The model name or model number of the equipment. This is the model name or "
"number of the DSC, scanner, video digitizer or other equipment that "
"generated the image. When the field is left blank, it is treated as unknown."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:160
msgid "New Subfile Type"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:160
msgid "A general indication of the kind of data contained in this subfile."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:161
msgid "OECF"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:161
msgid ""
"The Opto-Electronic Conversion Function (OECF) specified in ISO 14524. "
"<Exif.OECF> is the relationship between the camera optical input and the "
"image values."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:79 plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:162
msgid "Orientation"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:162
msgid "The image orientation viewed in terms of rows and columns."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:163
msgid "Photometric Interpretation"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:163
msgid ""
"The pixel composition. In JPEG compressed data a JPEG marker is used instead"
" of this tag."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:100
msgid "Pixel X Dimension"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:100
msgid ""
"Information specific to compressed data. When a compressed file is recorded,"
" the valid width of the meaningful image must be recorded in this tag, "
"whether or not there is padding data or a restart marker. This tag should "
"not exist in an uncompressed file."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:101
msgid "Pixel Y Dimension"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:101
msgid ""
"Information specific to compressed data. When a compressed file is recorded,"
" the valid height of the meaningful image must be recorded in this tag, "
"whether or not there is padding data or a restart marker. This tag should "
"not exist in an uncompressed file. Since data padding is unnecessary in the "
"vertical direction, the number of lines recorded in this valid image height "
"tag will in fact be the same as that recorded in the SOF."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:164
msgid "Planar Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:164
msgid ""
"Indicates whether pixel components are recorded in a chunky or planar "
"format. In JPEG compressed files a JPEG marker is used instead of this tag. "
"If this field does not exist, the TIFF default of 1 (chunky) is assumed."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:165
msgid "Primary Chromaticities"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:165
msgid ""
"The chromaticity of the three primary colors of the image. Normally this tag"
" is not necessary, since colorspace is specified in <Exif.ColorSpace> tag."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:166
msgid "Reference Black/White"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:166
msgid ""
"The reference black point value and reference white point value. No defaults"
" are given in TIFF, but the values below are given as defaults here. The "
"color space is declared in a color space information tag, with the default "
"being the value that gives the optimal image characteristics under these "
"conditions."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:167
msgid "Related Image File Format"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:167
msgid "Related image file format."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:168
msgid "Related Image Length"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:168
msgid "Related image length."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:169
msgid "Related Image Width"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:169
msgid "Related image width."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:170
msgid "Related Sound File"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:171
msgid "Resolution Unit"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:171
msgid ""
"The unit for measuring <Exif.XResolution> and <Exif.YResolution>. The same "
"unit is used for both <Exif.XResolution> and <Exif.YResolution>. If the "
"image resolution is unknown, 2 (inches) is designated."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:172
msgid "Rows per Strip"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:172
msgid ""
"The number of rows per strip. This is the number of rows in the image of one"
" strip when an image is divided into strips. With JPEG compressed data this "
"designation is not needed and is omitted."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:173
msgid "Samples per Pixel"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:173
msgid ""
"The number of components per pixel. Since this standard applies to RGB and "
"YCbCr images, the value set for this tag is 3. In JPEG compressed data a "
"JPEG marker is used instead of this tag."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:174
msgid "Saturation"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:174
msgid ""
"The direction of saturation processing applied by the camera when the image "
"was shot."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:175
msgid "Scene Capture Type"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:175
msgid ""
"The type of scene that was shot. It can also be used to record the mode in "
"which the image was shot. Note that this differs from <Exif.SceneType> tag."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:176
msgid "Scene Type"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:176
msgid ""
"The type of scene. If a DSC recorded the image, this tag value must always "
"be set to 1, indicating that the image was directly photographed."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:177
msgid "Sensing Method"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:177
msgid "The image sensor type on the camera or input device."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:178
msgid "Sharpness"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:178
msgid ""
"The direction of sharpness processing applied by the camera when the image "
"was shot."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:98
msgid "Shutter Speed"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:98
msgid ""
"Shutter speed. The unit is the APEX (Additive System of Photographic "
"Exposure) setting."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:80 plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:179
msgid "Software"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:179
msgid ""
"This tag records the name and version of the software or firmware of the "
"camera or image input device used to generate the image. When the field is "
"left blank, it is treated as unknown."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:180
msgid "Spatial Frequency Response"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:180
msgid ""
"This tag records the camera or input device spatial frequency table and SFR "
"values in the direction of image width, image height, and diagonal "
"direction, as specified in ISO 12233."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:181
msgid "Spectral Sensitivity"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:181
msgid "The spectral sensitivity of each channel of the camera used."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:182
msgid "Strip Byte Count"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:182
msgid ""
"The total number of bytes in each strip. With JPEG compressed data this "
"designation is not needed and is omitted."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:183
msgid "Strip Offsets"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:183
msgid ""
"For each strip, the byte offset of that strip. It is recommended that this "
"be selected so the number of strip bytes does not exceed 64 Kbytes. With "
"JPEG compressed data this designation is not needed and is omitted."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:184
msgid "Sub IFD Offsets"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:184
msgid "Defined by Adobe Corporation to enable TIFF Trees within a TIFF file."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:185
msgid "Subject Area"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:185
msgid "The location and area of the main subject in the overall scene."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:186
msgid "Subject Distance"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:186
msgid "The distance to the subject, given in meters."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:187
msgid "Subject Distance Range"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:187
msgid "The distance to the subject."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:188
msgid "Subject Location"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:188
msgid ""
"The location of the main subject in the scene. The value of this tag "
"represents the pixel at the center of the main subject relative to the left "
"edge, prior to rotation processing as per the <Exif.Rotation> tag. The first"
" value indicates the X column number and second indicates the Y row number."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:189
msgid "Subsec Time"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:189
msgid "Fractions of seconds for the <Exif.DateTime> tag."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:190
msgid "Subsec Time Digitized"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:190
msgid "Fractions of seconds for the <Exif.DateTimeDigitized> tag."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:191
msgid "Subsec Time Original"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:191
msgid "Fractions of seconds for the <Exif.DateTimeOriginal> tag."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:192
msgid "TIFF/EP Standard ID"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:192
msgid "TIFF/EP Standard ID."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:193
msgid "Transfer Function"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:193
msgid ""
"A transfer function for the image, described in tabular style. Normally this"
" tag is not necessary, since color space is specified in <Exif.ColorSpace> "
"tag."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:194
msgid "Transfer Range"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:194
msgid "Transfer range."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:109
msgid "User Comment"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:82 plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:99
msgid "White Balance"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:99
msgid "The white balance mode set when the image was shot."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:195
msgid "White Point"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:195
msgid ""
"The chromaticity of the white point of the image. Normally this tag is not "
"necessary, since color space is specified in <Exif.ColorSpace> tag."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:196
msgid "XML Packet"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:196
msgid "XMP metadata."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:102
msgid "x Resolution"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:102
msgid ""
"The number of pixels per <Exif.ResolutionUnit> in the <Exif.ImageWidth> "
"direction. When the image resolution is unknown, 72 [dpi] is designated."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:197
msgid "YCbCr Coefficients"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:198
msgid "YCbCr Positioning"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:198
msgid ""
"The position of chrominance components in relation to the luminance "
"component. This field is designated only for JPEG compressed data or "
"uncompressed YCbCr data. The TIFF default is 1 (centered); but when Y:Cb:Cr "
"= 4:2:2 it is recommended that 2 (co-sited) be used to record data, in order"
" to improve the image quality when viewed on TV systems. When this field "
"does not exist, the reader shall assume the TIFF default. In the case of "
"Y:Cb:Cr = 4:2:0, the TIFF default (centered) is recommended. If the reader "
"does not have the capability of supporting both kinds of "
"<Exif.YCbCrPositioning>, it shall follow the TIFF default regardless of the "
"value in this field. It is preferable that readers be able to support both "
"centered and co-sited positioning."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:199
msgid "YCbCr Sub-Sampling"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:199
msgid ""
"The sampling ratio of chrominance components in relation to the luminance "
"component. In JPEG compressed data a JPEG marker is used instead of this "
"tag."
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:103
msgid "y Resolution"
msgstr ""

#: plugins/exiv2/exiv2-plugin.cc:103
msgid ""
"The number of pixels per <Exif.ResolutionUnit> in the <Exif.ImageLength> "
"direction. The same value as <Exif.XResolution> is designated."
msgstr ""

